Class GPScoordinates

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network.GPScoordinates

  • public class GPScoordinates
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines the GPS coordinates of an element. It is here used to determine the location of a Station, or of a user.

      • distanceTo

        public double distanceTo(GPScoordinates pointB)
        This method calculates the distance in kilometers between two points, given their GPS coordinates. This method uses the Haversine formula to calculate the distance. The Haversine formula is used to determine the great-circle distance between two points on a sphere of known radius, given their latitudes and longitudes.
        Parameters:
        pointB - the point to which the distance should be calculated to.
        Returns:
        the distance between the 2 points, in km.
